{
  "texts": [
    "This high efficiency, together with the high fidelity of KGML-ag-Carbon to observational data, may facilitate the large-scale high-resolution multi-scenario assessment of management practices and spatially explicit parameter optimization, with some modifications to including the responses from carbon cycles to certain management practices or ecosys parameters.",
    "We used the agroecosystem model ecosys to generate synthetic data for crop yield, ecosystem autotrophic respiration (Ra), ecosystem heterotrophic respiration (Rh), net ecosystem exchange (NEE), and gross primary production (GPP).",
    "This synthetic data was used to pretrain the Knowledge-Guided Machine Learning for the Agricultural Carbon budget model (KGML-ag-Carbon).",
    "Ecosys simultaneously simulates carbon, water, and nutrient cycles within the soil and plant system based on biophysical and biochemical principles 29.",
    "Its ability to simulate carbon fluxes and crop yields has been extensively validated across midwestern U.S. cropping systems 13."
  ]
}